did.physdesc: Records, guest books, video tour, card files, financial records, and correspondence.
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Records, files, and miscellany relating to the Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections.

bioghist.head: ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY
bioghist.p: The Division was formed in 1992 with the combination of the Department of Rare Books, the Department of Manuscripts and University Archives, the History of Science Collections, and the Icelandic Collection.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Administrative records of the Division; also book truck labels fancifully annotated by student employees during the transfer of collections from Olin Library to Kroch Library, and guest books signed by early visitors and patrons, August through November, 1992; a video tour of the Division created by Nancy Dean. Icelandic Collection circulation and other card files; records of the Division's Strategic Plan, 1993-94; financial records of the Division; chronological file of outgoing correspondence; magneto-optical disk (MOD) backups; and Division exhibit items, records, and related material. Records compiled by Cheryl Stadel-Bevans, 1998-1999 for an 18-month NHPRC (National Historical Publications and Records Commission)-sponsored project to investigate the requirements for electronic administrative records at Cornell, and a report by Nancy McGovern on electronic student records systems, 2000. Files relating to the John Nolen Research Fund, 1990-2001.
